description:
&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 900;&quot;&gt;Work from anywhere, impact everywhere&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diversity is at the heart of who we are at Xapo Bank. We‚Äôre a fully distributed team of over 140 Xapiens that work remotely from 40+ countries around the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our beginning: A world that enjoys economic freedom and wealth protection, no matter where you live or who is running your country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve that, we search the world for the best people for the job. We work hard, think globally, and inspire each other to learn and grow. We are committed to changing the way things are done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk is inherent in all of our business activities and managing risk well is the responsibility of every Xapien. Sound risk management enables us to serve our customers and deliver value for our shareholders, and helps make Xapo a great place to work.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Although we are headquartered in Gibraltar, this is a full time, 100% remote position&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Work from anywhere!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Position overview&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Content Specialist, reporting into the VP of Marketing, will play a crucial role in developing and executing Xapo Bank‚Äôs content strategy to drive brand awareness, engagement, and ultimately, conversions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement a comprehensive content marketing strategy that aligns with the company‚Äôs growth objectives and brand positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead SEO efforts to increase visibility and organic search rankings, collaborating closely with web developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage content production across various formats including blogs, white papers, video, and social media, ensuring all content is on-brand, consistent in terms of style, quality, and tone of voice, and optimized for search and user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the editorial calendar and ensure content is scheduled, produced, and published in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze content marketing data and SEO performance to continually refine strategies and tactics, maximizing effectiveness and ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the content and design for Xapo Bank&#39;s website&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including product, PR, and digital marketing, to create synergies and leverage content across all channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and expand the content marketing team, nurturing talent and developing skills to meet evolving market and organizational demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster relationships with key influencers, thought leaders, and external partners to amplify outreach and content distribution efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current with industry trends and competitor strategies to ensure that our content is ahead of the curve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Skills needed:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid experience in a similar role spanning content and organic marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Marketing, Communications, Journalism, or a related field. Advanced degree preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in content marketing and SEO, with a strong track record of enhancing organic search and engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Video content creation, video production and editing skills would be highly beneficial.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with an ability to interpret data to make informed content decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional writing and editing skills, with a keen understanding of what resonates with target audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with content management systems, SEO tools (e.g., SEMrush, Ahrefs), and analytics platforms (e.g., GA4, Search Console).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience having worked in the Crypto industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Other requirements&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated workspace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A reliable internet connection with the fastest speed possible in your area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Devices and other essential equipment that meet minimal technical specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alignment with Our Values and the Xapo Values-Driven Leadership principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why work for Xapo?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;IMPACT GLOBALLY, WORK REMOTELY.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape the Future:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; Improve lives through cutting-edge technology, work 100% remotely from anywhere in the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Great work-life balance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Build amazing things with a balance of autonomy and collaborative teamwork. Set your own work schedule and make use of a flexible PTO plan when you need to recharge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expect Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; Collaborate, learn, and grow with a high-performance team. Learn&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; how you learn best - from books to conferences, you‚Äôll get a yearly budget for your individual learning and development goals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At Xapo, we prioritize consumer protection and adhere to regulatory requirements by ensuring that all Xapiens are accountable for upholding principles of fair treatment, transparency, and ethical conduct in their interactions with customers and stakeholders.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Xapo Device Policy&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Consultants joining Xapo Bank must comply with the Xapo Device Policy, which governs the use of corporate-approved laptops under Corporate-Owned, Personally Purchased Device (reimbursed up to $1,500) or Corporate-Owned, Personally Enabled Device (personal device with enforced security controls).&lt;br&gt;All devices must meet security requirements, enroll in Xapo‚Äôs Mobile Device Management (MDM), and adhere to compliance rules. COPPD devices remain Xapo property with buyback options upon exit. COPED users agree to data control measures, including mandatory corporate data wipes.&lt;br&gt;Compliance with the Xapo Device Policy is mandatory for all consultants, onboarding will not proceed without adherence to the policy.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 900;&quot;&gt;Work from anywhere, impact everywhere&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diversity is at the heart of who we are at Xapo Bank. We‚Äôre a fully distributed team of over 140 Xapiens that work remotely from 40+ countries around the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our beginning: A world that enjoys economic freedom and wealth protection, no matter where you live or who is running your country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve that, we search the world for the best people for the job. We work hard, think globally, and inspire each other to learn and grow. We are committed to changing the way things are done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk is inherent in all of our business activities and managing risk well is the responsibility of every Xapien. Sound risk management enables us to serve our customers and deliver value for our shareholders, and helps make Xapo a great place to work.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Although we are headquartered in Gibraltar, this is a full time, 100% remote position&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Work from anywhere!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Position overview&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Xapo, we believe in empowering our software engineering teams with a world-class &lt;strong&gt;cloud-native application platform&lt;/strong&gt;. Such a platform automates infrastructure provisioning and configuration, dynamically allocating resources based on application needs. This approach optimizes the entire application lifecycle, enabling efficient scaling, superior resource utilization, seamless orchestration, and rapid recovery from failures with minimal downtime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By standardizing how software is built and deployed, our platform reduces cognitive load on development teams, allowing them to focus on delivering value. This standardization also streamlines onboarding for new engineers and teams. The Platform Engineering Team (PET) is central to this, not only by building and maintaining the platform but also by mentoring and supporting development teams in leveraging cloud-native best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is for development teams to consume core platform services in a self-service, autonomous manner. These services are the products of the Platform Engineering Team and include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure Provisioning:&lt;/strong&gt; Self-service access to compute, network, and storage resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CI/CD &amp;amp; Developer Tooling:&lt;/strong&gt; Robust, automated pipelines and the underlying tools that enable rapid and reliable software delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Observability Suite:&lt;/strong&gt; Comprehensive tools and practices for logging, monitoring, metrics, and alerting across all environments, ensuring high availability, resilience, and actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure as Code (IaC) Frameworks:&lt;/strong&gt; Standardized, reusable patterns and tools for creating and managing services in line with agreed architectural best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platform Engineering is a critical pillar at Xapo, providing the foundational technology for our innovative financial products. We are seeking a pragmatic and influential Head of Platform Engineering to lead our dedicated team. This role is pivotal in continuously advancing our platform as a product, championing developer productivity and autonomy, and ensuring robust, scalable, secure, and cost-effective operations. You will report directly to the CTO.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Your Role &amp;amp; Responsibilities: Leading the Platform Evolution&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Head of Platform Engineering, you will embody a &lt;strong&gt;product mindset&lt;/strong&gt;, treating our internal engineering community as your primary customers. Your mission is to deliver a platform that they love to use, enabling them to build and iterate rapidly and safely. You will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead &amp;amp; Mentor:&lt;/strong&gt; Directly manage and cultivate a small, high-performing team of 4 Platform Engineers. Foster a collaborative, innovative, and results-oriented culture with a strong sense of ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Roadmap &amp;amp; Vision:&lt;/strong&gt; Define, articulate, and drive the strategic vision and product roadmap for the Xapo platform, ensuring alignment with business objectives and engineering needs. Prioritize initiatives that deliver maximum business impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platform as a Product:&lt;/strong&gt; Champion the &quot;Platform as a Product&quot; approach, deeply understanding developer needs, gathering feedback, and iteratively improving platform services to enhance developer experience and autonomy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hands-On Technical Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide technical guidance and be prepared to be hands-on when needed, contributing to design, architecture, and complex problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence &amp;amp; Automation:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive the sustainable maintenance, operability, and evolution of our developer platform. Champion cloud-native principles, relentless automation, robust testing of changes, and Infrastructure as Code (IaC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disaster Recovery &amp;amp; Business Continuity:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop, implement, and regularly test disaster recovery plans for all platform services, ensuring business continuity and minimizing data loss in the event of an outage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audit Support &amp;amp; Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively prepare for and support internal and external audits by providing necessary documentation, evidence of controls, and subject matter expertise related to platform infrastructure, security, and operations. Ensure platform practices align with relevant compliance requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Enablement:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with the Engineering Enablement team, treating them as an extension of the platform effort, to ensure seamless integration of best practices, tools, and training. Partner effectively with all engineering teams and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build vs. Buy Decisions:&lt;/strong&gt; Make pragmatic decisions on technology adoption, favoring SaaS and managed services where appropriate (&quot;favor buy over build and SaaS over on-prem&quot;) while ensuring we only operate what is absolutely essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feedback &amp;amp; Iteration:&lt;/strong&gt; Implement and manage mechanisms for providing high-quality, fast feedback to development teams on platform usage, performance, and upcoming features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Future-Proof Architecture:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure the platform is architected to handle change effectively, whether from new services, evolving customer needs, regulatory requirements, new tooling, or shifts in demand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vendor &amp;amp; Budget Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage relationships with key technology vendors and contribute to budget planning for platform-related expenses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring: Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a leader who is passionate about building great platforms and enabling other engineers to succeed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Demonstrable experience leading, managing, and mentoring engineering teams, ideally in a platform, DevOps, or SRE capacity. Experience with small, agile, and flat-structured teams is highly beneficial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platform Product Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; A strong understanding of and practical experience with &quot;Platform as a Product&quot; principles and applying a product management mindset to internal platforms. Familiarity with concepts like Team Topologies is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developer Empathy &amp;amp; Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; A genuine passion for improving developer experience, productivity, and autonomy. Proven ability to design and support software and/or platforms that are actively used and valued by other developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Depth &amp;amp; Breadth:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive hands-on experience in running and scaling platforms within a DevOps culture, including delivering and operating a comprehensive DevOps toolchain and automation frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong, demonstrable experience in designing, building, and maintaining CI/CD pipelines and supporting technologies (e.g., Jenkins, GitLab CI, GitHub Actions, ArgoCD).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep technical knowledge across software development, systems architecture, cloud infrastructure (preferably AWS), containerization (Kubernetes), IaC (e.g., Terraform, Pulumi), and observability (e.g., Prometheus, Grafana, ELK Stack).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic &amp;amp; Pragmatic Thinking:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to translate high-level business and engineering strategy into a clear platform roadmap, making pragmatic decisions that balance innovation with operational stability and business impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build vs. Buy Acumen:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience integrating with third-party SaaS providers and a clear, demonstrable understanding of how to evaluate build versus buy decisions effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent Communication &amp;amp; Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to dive into technical details with engineers and distill complex information for executive and non-technical audiences. Proven ability to collaborate effectively across teams and influence without direct authority.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Learner:&lt;/strong&gt; Stays abreast of current technology developments, industry best practices, and emerging trends, with a demonstrated ability to identify and implement relevant technologies to maintain a competitive advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Other requirements&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated workspace&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A reliable internet connection with the fastest speed possible in your area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Devices and other essential equipment that meet minimal technical specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alignment with Our Values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why work for Xapo?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;IMPACT GLOBALLY, WORK REMOTELY.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shape the Future:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; Improve lives through cutting-edge technology, work 100% remotely from anywhere in the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Great work-life balance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Build amazing things with a balance of autonomy and collaborative teamwork. Set your own work schedule and make use of a flexible PTO plan when you need to recharge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expect Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; Collaborate, learn, and grow with a high-performance team. Learn&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt; how you learn best - from books to conferences, you‚Äôll get a yearly budget for your individual learning and development goals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At Xapo, we prioritize consumer protection and adhere to regulatory requirements by ensuring that all Xapiens are accountable for upholding principles of fair treatment, transparency, and ethical conduct in their interactions with customers and stakeholders.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Xapo Device Policy&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Consultants joining Xapo Bank must comply with the Xapo Device Policy, which governs the use of corporate-approved laptops under Corporate-Owned, Personally Purchased Device (reimbursed up to $1,500) or Corporate-Owned, Personally Enabled Device (personal device with enforced security controls).&lt;br&gt;All devices must meet security requirements, enroll in Xapo‚Äôs Mobile Device Management (MDM), and adhere to compliance rules. COPPD devices remain Xapo property with buyback options upon exit. COPED users agree to data control measures, including mandatory corporate data wipes.&lt;br&gt;Compliance with the Xapo Device Policy is mandatory for all consultants, onboarding will not proceed without adherence to the policy.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 900;&quot;&gt;Work from anywhere, impact everywhere&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diversity is at the heart of who we are at Xapo Bank. We‚Äôre a fully distributed team of over 140 Xapiens that work remotely from 40+ countries around the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our beginning: A world that enjoys economic freedom and wealth protection, no matter where you live or who is running your country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To achieve that, we search the world for the best people for the job. We work hard, think globally, and inspire each other to learn and grow. We are committed to changing the way things are done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk is inherent in all of our business activities and managing risk well is the responsibility of every Xapien. Sound risk management enables us to serve our customers and deliver value for our shareholders, and helps make Xapo a great place to work.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Although we are headquartered in Gibraltar, this is a full time, 100% remote position&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 500;&quot;&gt;Work from anywhere!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Position overview&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an enthusiastic and detail-oriented FP&amp;amp;A Graduate to join our growing Finance team. This is an exciting opportunity to gain hands-on experience in financial planning, forecasting, and analysis, directly contributing to our strategic decision-making. The ideal candidate will have a strong academic foundation in a relevant field, a keen interest in data and the crypto space, and a proactive attitude towards learning and development in a dynamic environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Graduate Programme runs for a period of 12 months giving successful graduates the opportunity to become a full time Xapien once the programme has concluded. This role would therefore be a 12 month contract.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation of monthly, quarterly, and annual financial forecasts and budgets, learning the underlying processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the analysis of financial data to identify initial trends and provide supporting insights for business decisions, under guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help prepare and distribute regular financial reports, including variance analysis and performance summaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and maintenance of financial models and forecasting tools, learning best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation of presentations for senior management and stakeholders, gaining exposure to executive communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ad-hoc financial analysis and reporting as required, developing your analytical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the preparation of business cases for new initiatives and investments, learning the financial evaluation process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather financial data, focusing on accuracy and understanding data sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn to monitor and track key performance indicators (KPIs) and contribute to identifying areas for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with aspects of the month-end and year-end closing processes, gaining insight into accounting cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the continuous improvement of FP&amp;amp;A processes and procedures by identifying areas for learning and suggesting improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Skills needed&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Excel/ Google Sheets, with a willingness to develop financial modeling and data analysis skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with basic financial reporting and accounting concepts gained through academic studies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to learn to present findings clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively both independently and as part of a team, demonstrating a proactive approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and a commitment to accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuine interest in fintech and the crypto space, with a desire to learn about the financial services industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with financial planning software (e.g., Anaplan), ERP software (e.g., NetSuite), or data software (e.g., Looker) gained through academic projects is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of SQL or other database querying languages learned through coursework is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate effectively with team members and stakeholders, with a willingness to learn from others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eagerness to learn and develop new financial skills and knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to Detail - demonstrates a methodical approach to tasks and a focus on accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Other requirements&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated workspace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A reliable internet connection with the fastest speed possible in your area.&lt;/li&gt;
